                            <comment id="17514974" author="emilles" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2022 22:26:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is affected by the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8409&quot; title=&quot;Static compilation with generic function wrapping BiFunction causes GroovyCastException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8409&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8409&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; mixing of generics contexts.  One workaround you can make use of to avoid this is to use another type parameter name: &quot;def &amp;lt;X&amp;gt; X m(Function&amp;lt;Reader, X&amp;gt; f)&quot;.  R, S, T and U are in common usage.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am working on backporting some sort of fix.  But the 8409 changes are very large and risky, so I cannot take them as they are.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
